so understanding timestamps in the postgresql database 

uniz time is timezone dependent 


so theres two 

TIMESTAMP and TIMESTAMZ 



pretty simple 

TIMESTAMP 
date + time, but no timezone information
2026-07-10 23:15:00

TIMESTAMPZ 
timestamp with timezone awareness
2026-07-10 23:15:00+09


SO WE RECOMMEND USING TIMESTAMZ !


in sql below:

created_at TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW()
